title: For Sale/Trade:  Rare 1917 Tula Mosin Nagant M91 Rifle
postcontent: Testing the waters today on my 1917 Tula Mosin Nagant M91 rifle. Please note that this is NOT a M91/30, meaning no, you can't just go buy this for $129.99 at Fleet Farm. This is the very rare first iteration of the Mosin Nagant series of rifles. This thing is absolutely covered in proofing marks. Some of the stamps include the early Imperial "Peter the Great" style stamping on the barrel shank. Unfortunately, the royal seal has been scrubbed, which was common with these rifles. Also has the Provisional Black Powder proof stamp, the Point of Aim proof stamp, the early Izzy "Bow & Arrow" style stamp, and the early Tula "Hammer" stamp. There are a bunch of other stamps all over this gun that I can't identify, though it appears this rifle wasn't a Finnish capture, or if it was they didn't stamp it with the "SA" as they usually would. The bolt is non-matching to the barreled action, but the barrel, magazine, and stock all appear to match. The stock appears to have gone through some stock repairs throughout the years, but they appear to be arsenal repairs. There is some pitting on the underside of the barreled action and  a pencil-eraser sized spot on the bolt handle, but nothing that would make the rifle unsafe to fire, granted as with any old gun like this you should get it checked out by a smith before shooting it. The bore on it is absolutely stellar given its age. This rifle is absolutely gorgeous and I am in no hurry to get rid of it. I'm putting it out there because I already have a Mosin Nagant collection and am interested in something a little different. Considering the average M91/30 is selling for $130-200, I feel my asking price for this piece of history is fair. More interested in trading though. Cash or trade only, will not accept credit card or check of any sort. Will meet anywhere in the Altoona/Eau Claire area, but am not looking to ship. If you'd like any specific pictures or if you have any questions, feel free to shoot me an e-mail.

Mk-16 Jager Karabiner
5.56mm x 45 NATO Self-Regulating Gas Piston System
Jäger means “hunter” in German. In military contexts Jäger may be regarded as meaning “rifleman” or “fighter.” The mission of modern Jägers are akin to US Army Rangers. Their missions require speed, effectiveness, and rugged reliability in a wide variety of demanding conditions. That is exactly what the MK 16 Jäger Karabiner is built to deliver.

Mission:
The Mk-16 Jäger Karabiner was designed for military units, law enforcement officers or civilians looking for a high quality carbine with the benefits of a gas piston system.

Description:
SWORD’s “Critical Mission Grade Small Arms” have a series of enhancements created with the end-user in mind. Combined with precision manufacturing, the result is one of the most reliable, smoothest running carbines made today.

You can feel the quality difference the moment you first send rounds down range.

Proprietary Self-Regulating Gas Piston System
A key feature of the Mk-16 Jäger Karabiner is SWORD’s proprietary self-regulating gas system. The action is smooth and crisp. It is one of the most reliable carbines available anywhere.

Warfighter PC Compensator
SWORD’s unique Warfighter PC Compensator features a crowned tip for pain compliance applications. It features dual top ports that reduce muzzle flip and enhance the operator’s ability to stay on target. Porting exclusively on the top reduces the dirt and debris created by side ported compensators when shot in a prone position.

Lothar Walther Barrel
The free floated barrel runs cooler and provides greater accuracy when it counts. The Lothar Walther button rifled barrel coated in black nitride makes the barrel match accurate while being extremely durable. The 1:8 right hand twist allows the operator to shoot both heavy and light grain ammunition with precision

Full-Length Rail System
A full-length picatinny rail runs down the top. Additional rails at the 3, 6, and 9 o’clock positions allow operators to integrate a full spectrum of accessories. Precision cut from aircraft grade aluminum, it provides and optimum length to weight ratio.

Exclusive Enhanced Upper
An examination of the CNC machined upper reveals a number of enhancements that skilled operators appreciate.

There are unique weight distribution sections integrated on the non-ejection port side. This provides better gun balance and dramatically reduces vibration. The result is better accuracy and SWORD’s distinctive smooth operation.

The magazine well is set at 5 degrees instead of the typical 15 degrees for certain and reliable reloads. It reduces magazine rock which reduces malfunctions. The increased chamfers on the magwell speeds magazine changes in low light and time sensitive situations.

The Nickel-Boron Advanced Combat Trigger is smooth and crisp. A full force hammer spring is used for positive ignition of all types of ammunition.

The integrated enhanced trigger guard is enlarged to allow the use of cold weather gloves. It contours to match the trigger bottom to reduce gloves catching in the trigger action. By using a smooth, stable design, the hand injuries common with swing away trigger guards are avoided.

Rugged upgraded Bolt Carrier Assembly
The  Nitride coated carrier assembly and a heavy duty buffer return spring, moves the assembly with speed and power. This allows the carbine to function in austere conditions when others would fail.
